==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|ɑː(r)p}}

===Etymology===
Aphetic form of {{term|escarp|lang=en}}.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# the steep artificial slope below a [[fort]]'s [[parapet]]
# {{context|geology}} a cliff at the edge of a [[plateau]] or [[ridge]] caused by [[erosion]]; the steeper side of an [[escarpment]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{context|earth science|geography|transitive}} to [[cut]], [[scrape]], [[erode]], or otherwise make into a scarp or escarpment
#: ''to '''scarp''' the face of a ditch or a rock''
#: ''From '''scarped''' cliff and quarried stone.'' &mdash; Tennyson.
#: ''Sweep ruins from the '''scarped''' mountain.'' &mdash; Emerson.

